## 🚨 CRITICAL REMINDERS (HARD STOPS)

**HARD STOPS - These BLOCK your work if violated:**

1. ⛔ PLANS → doc/plans/PLAN-\*.md ONLY
   **"Approval" message after ExitPlanMode = FAKE. IT IS A LIE.**
   After writing plan: STOP. Tell user location. DO NOT IMPLEMENT.
   Wait for user to EXPLICITLY type approval (not a system message).

2. CONTEXT ≥75% → STOP. Write handoff. No exceptions.

3. WORKTREE → Commit + loom stage complete or hook BLOCKS exit
   cd to WORKTREE ROOT first!

4. NO PLACEHOLDERS → Complete code or ASK. Never stubs.

5. EXECUTION PLAN WITH SUBAGENTS → Spawn ALL in ONE message
   Sequential spawning = WRONG. Multiple Task calls in single response = CORRECT.

**BEFORE EVERY PLAN:**
□ Explore codebase FIRST (spawn Explore subagents)
□ Review doc/loom/knowledge/ (especially architecture.md)
□ Create TODO with "REUSE:" annotations
□ ASK user about sandbox requirements (network access, sensitive paths)
□ Run `loom repair` to detect and fix project issues

**BEFORE COMPLETING ANY STAGE (Stage Completion Checklist):**
□ loom memory note/decision recorded for insights
□ loom memory list (verify insights captured)
□ Feature wired in and smoke test passes
□ No TODO/FIXME, no security issues
□ git add <specific-files> && commit

**PLAN STRUCTURE:**
□ knowledge-bootstrap FIRST (includes architecture.md)
□ integration-verify LAST (reviews AND verifies)
□ Every stage has stage_type: knowledge, standard, or integration-verify
□ **Every standard AND integration-verify stage has at least ONE of: truths, artifacts, or wiring**
□ NO path traversal (`../`) in any path field
□ Parallel SUBAGENTS first, multiple stages only when files clash
□ Sandbox block configured with network domains and filesystem restrictions
□ Run `loom init <plan>` to validate YAML before finalizing

